# Add Electronic Product Displays Section (3-day Expiry) and Admin Management Panel

This plan outlines the design and implementation steps for adding a new electronic products section on the public homepage. Admins can create and delete these posts via a new dashboard sub-panel. Each post is set to be active for 3 days and displays a product image, name, and cost. When a customer clicks on the product, they are redirected to the admin's WhatsApp with a pre-filled message indicating interest in that specific product.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> - **Product Images**: Admins will upload images directly from the dashboard. To prevent performance and database bloat issues, images will be restricted to a maximum size of **2MB** and stored as Base64 text in the PostgreSQL database (consistent with the existing promotion deals implementation).
> - **Expirations**: The active products will only display on the public landing page if they were created within the last 3 days. An automated badge will show the remaining time (e.g., "Expires in 2d 12h") on both the homepage cards and the admin management panel.
> - **Layout Placement**: The section is configured to display on the landing page (`index.html`) directly below the Services section and above the Footer. If there are no active listings, the section is hidden completely to keep the landing page clean.

